annotations.title: NASA's Perseverance rover lands on Mars
NASA's Mars helicopter takes flight as first aircraft piloted on another planet

content.text:
- **Perseverance rover landing (Feb. 18, 2021):** NASAs Perseverance rover safely touched down in Mars Jezero Crater, an ancient lakebed, to begin its mission of searching for signs of past microbial life and collecting rock samples for a future return to Earth ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/02/18/nasa-perseverance-rover-lands-mars#:~:text=NASA%27s%20Perseverance%20rover%20successfully%20landed,a%20future%20mission%2C%20slated%20for)).  
- **Ingenuity helicopters first flight (Apr. 19, 2021):** NASAs Ingenuity drone completed the first-ever controlled, powered flight on another planet by briefly hovering on Mars, proving that aerial exploration is possible on the Red Planet ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/04/19/nasa-ingenuity-mars-helicopter-first-flight#:~:text=NASA%27s%20Ingenuity%20Mars%20helicopter%20made,This%20milestone%20paves%20the)).
